text: Kiera Van Ryk (born 6 January 1999 in New Westminster) is a Canadian female volleyball player. She is part of the Canadian women's national volleyball team. She participated at the 2018 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship, 2018 Women's Pan-American Volleyball Cup, and 2019 FIVB Volleyball Women's Challenger Cup. She played for the University of British Columbia's women's volleyball team and Volley Bergamo. == References == Category:1999 births Category:Living people Category:Canadian volleyball players Category:University of British Columbia alumni
